  "prompt": "Can I use WhatsApp with a different number than the cell phone I have it installed in without changing sims just adding the other number?",
  "response": "Yes, you can use WhatsApp with a different number than the one associated with the SIM card in your phone. WhatsApp allows you to register and use the app with any phone number, regardless of the SIM card that is currently in your device. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Download and Install WhatsApp:** If you haven't already installed WhatsApp, download it from the App Store or Google Play Store and install it on your phone.\n\n2. **Verification Step:** When you open WhatsApp, you will be prompted to enter a phone number to verify your account. Enter the phone number that you want to use with WhatsApp. This number can be different from the one on your SIM card.\n\n3. **Receive Verification Code:** WhatsApp will send a verification code to the phone number you provided. You need to have access to this number to receive the SMS or call containing the verification code.\n\n4. **Enter Verification Code:** Once you receive the code, enter it into WhatsApp to verify the number.\n\n5. **Complete Setup:** After verifying the number, complete the setup process, and you can start using WhatsApp with the different phone number.\n\nKeep in mind:\n- You need to have access to the phone number you want to use, at least temporarily, to receive the verification code.\n- Your WhatsApp account will be linked to the phone number you registered, and that number will be displayed to your contacts.\n\nYou can then continue using WhatsApp on your device with the registered number, even if the SIM card inserted into the phone has a different number.",
